---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import DocNav from "../components/DocNav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { strings } from "../lib/i18n";

const lastUpdated = "2026-04-22";
const meta = strings.en.meta;
---
<Base title={meta.termsTitle} description={meta.termsDescription}>
  <DocNav />
  <article
    class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16"
    style="color: var(--color-zeed-text)"
  >
    <h1 class="mb-2 text-4xl">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="mb-10 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-zeed-muted)">
      Last updated: {lastUpdated}
    </p>

    <section class="space-y-10 leading-relaxed">
      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl">1. Scope</h2>
        <p>
          These terms govern use of the browser software Zeed Browser
          (the "Software") provided by EFG Technologies Inc. (the "Company").
          Installing or using the Software constitutes acceptance of these
          terms.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl">2. License</h2>
        <p>
          The Software is distributed under Mozilla Public License 2.0
          ("MPL-2.0"). Source code is available on
          <a href="https://github.com/efg-technologies/zeed-browser">GitHub</a>.
          Reproduction, modification, and redistribution are permitted within
          the license.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl">3. Agent autonomy and responsibility</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          The Software's Agent feature operates websites on your behalf
          based on your instructions. Note:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>
            <strong>Sensitive actions require explicit approval.</strong>
            Form submission, purchase, publishing, deletion, authentication,
            and payment all prompt for confirmation before executing. None
            complete silently.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Agent is disabled in Private mode.</strong>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Final decisions and responsibility rest with the user.</strong>
            Outcomes of Agent actions (incorrect orders, misdirected messages,
            accidental deletions) are considered user-authorized, and the
            Company is not liable for them.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>You must follow third-party site terms.</strong>
            Using Agent to bypass anti-scraping or anti-automation policies
            is your responsibility.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl">4. LLM and external APIs</h2>
        <p>
          The Software's AI features send requests directly to LLM providers
          through the OpenRouter API key you configure. The Company does not
          relay or retain this traffic. LLM usage fees are paid by you
          directly to the provider. The Company makes no warranty as to
          correctness or legality of LLM output.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl">5. Pricing (planned)</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Today (Phase 1) the Software is distributed <strong>free</strong>.
          Planned tiers:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>
            <strong>Zeed Local (free)</strong> — BYO OpenRouter key, all
            local features, single-device use.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Zeed Plus ($5/mo, planned)</strong> — adds multi-device
            sync, OS-level cron, email ingress, priority support.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Zeed Pro ($10/mo, planned)</strong> — adds managed LLM,
            3× cron execution budget, first-party Agent plugins.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Timing and pricing of paid tiers may change without notice.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl">6. Affiliate disclosure</h2>
        <p>
          In a future Phase 7, the Agent may append affiliate tags to URLs
          from Amazon, Rakuten, booking sites, etc. in user-visible search
          results. When it does, the Agent will surface the URL, and the
          user can disable the behavior in settings at any time. The Company
          consumes only <strong>anonymous aggregate click data</strong> —
          no personally identifiable information.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl">7. Prohibited uses</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
          <li>Using the Software for illegal acts, harassment, or copyright infringement.</li>
          <li>Using Agent to systematically evade a third-party site's terms.</li>
          <li>Exploiting vulnerabilities for any purpose other than good-faith security research (responsible disclosure is welcome).</li>
          <li>Commercial use of the Company's brand or logo without permission.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl">8. Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          The Software is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind,
          express or implied, including merchantability, fitness for a
          particular purpose, and non-infringement. To the extent permitted
          by law, the Company is not liable for damages (data loss, lost
          opportunity, indirect damages) arising from use of the Software.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl">9. Governing law and jurisdiction</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of Japan. Disputes arising
          from these terms or the Software are subject to the exclusive
          jurisdiction of the Tokyo District Court as the court of first
          instance. Mandatory consumer-protection provisions applicable to
          EU/UK users are unaffected.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl">10. Changes</h2>
        <p>
          The Company may revise these terms. Material changes are announced
          on the landing page and in GitHub release notes. Continued use of
          the Software after a revision constitutes acceptance of it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-2xl">11. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          <a href="mailto:support@efg-technologies.com">support@efg-technologies.com</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
  <Footer />
</Base>
